        "content": "<p>I think they are the same.</p>",
        "id": 340177906,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1678212538
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Described here:<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/master/doc/lean3changes.md#dependent-function-types\">https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/master/doc/lean3changes.md#dependent-function-types</a></p>",
        "id": 340178388,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1678212659
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also putting something as the last argument was always equivalent to putting it at the beginning of the theorem statement.</p>",
        "id": 340178694,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1678212738
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A different use of <code>forall</code> (denoted by <code>∀</code> usually) is in the middle of a theorem (over there, it cannot be written equivalently as an argument of the declaration).</p>",
        "id": 340179332,
